<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="26" type="basionym">
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="26">Basionym.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="26">
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Onagraceae" genus="Gaura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Gaura hispida" order="Myrtales" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="hispida">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">Gaura hispida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Bentham, Pl. Hartw. 288. 1840.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="27" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" type="type">
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="26">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">Type.</emphasis>
Mexico: In fields near Leon, Guanajuato, June 1837, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">Thomas Hartweg 1603</emphasis>
(Holotype: K! [Kew image]; Isotypes: BM, CAMB, G, LD!).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="26">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Spach" authorityYear="1835" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Onagraceae" genus="Schizocarya" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Schizocarya drummondii" order="Myrtales" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="drummondii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">Schizocarya drummondii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Spach, Nouv. Ann. Mus.Hist. Nat. 4: 382. 1836 [
<normalizedToken originalValue="“1835”">&quot;1835&quot;</normalizedToken>
]. 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Onagraceae" genus="Gaura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Gaura drummondii" order="Myrtales" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="drummondii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">Gaura drummondii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Spach) Torrey &amp; A. Gray, Fl. N. Amer. 1: 519. 1838. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="W. L. Wagner &amp; Hoch" authorityYear="2007" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Onagraceae" genus="Oenothera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Oenothera xenogaura" order="Myrtales" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="xenogaura">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">Oenothera xenogaura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
W.L.Wagner &amp; Hoch, Syst. Bot. Monogr. 83: 213. 2007.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">Type.</emphasis>
U.S.A. Texas: Travis Co., Austin, 1833-1834, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">T. Drummond III.36</emphasis>
(Holotype: G; isotypes: BM!, GH!, NY!, P). Note: the BM isotype is mounted on a sheet with two non-type collections of the same species: Purpus 3387 and Purpus 5383.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="26">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Scheele" authorityYear="1848" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Onagraceae" genus="Gaura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Gaura roemeriana" order="Myrtales" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="roemeriana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">Gaura roemeriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Scheele, Linnaea 21: 579. 1848.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">Type.</emphasis>
U.S.A. Texas: Comal Co., New Braunfels, 1846, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">Ferdinand Roemer s.n.</emphasis>
(Lectotype: MO-1833107!, here designated; Isolectotypes: CAS, HAL). The holotype at B was destroyed in World War II.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="26">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Spach" authorityYear="1835" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Onagraceae" genus="Schizocarya" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Schizocarya crispa" order="Myrtales" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="crispa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">Schizocarya crispa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Spach, Nouv. Ann. Mus. Paris 4: 384. 1835. 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Onagraceae" genus="Gaura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Gaura crispa" order="Myrtales" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="crispa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">Gaura crispa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Spach) D.Dietr., Syn. PI. 2: 1298. 1840.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">Type.</emphasis>
Mexico: Tamaulipas, Matamoros, April 1831, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">J. L. Berlandier 2313</emphasis>
(Holotype: G; Isotypes: BM, K, P).
</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="27" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">
Plant rhizomatous, perennial, forming extensive colonies, strigillose and often also villous. Stems 20-60(-120) cm tall, sometimes strict with a single unbranched main 
<pageBreakToken pageId="2" pageNumber="27" start="start">stem</pageBreakToken>
but usually somewhat decumbent with several branches from the base and usually irregular branching above. Leaves in a basal rosette and cauline, 0.5-7.5 (-9.5) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.1-2.2 cm; subsessile; blade narrowly lanceolate to elliptic, margin subentire to shallowly sinuate-dentate. Inflorescence a spike. Flowers 4-merous, zygomorphic, opening near sunset; floral tube 4-14 mm; sepals 7-11(-14) mm; petals white, fading red, 6-10 mm; staminal filaments 4-8.5 mm, anthers 3-6 mm; style 12-26 mm. Capsule 7-13 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3-5 mm, erect, the body ellipsoid or ovoid, 4-angled, distal half pyramidal, the base of the pyramidal portion distinctly bulging, then immediately and sharply constricted to the terete proximal part. Seeds (2-)3-4(-8), 2-2.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1-1.25 mm, ovoid, usually flattened on one or several sides by crowding in the fruit, reddish brown. 2n = 28.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="27" type="phenology and distribution">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="27">Phenology and distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="27">
Flowering from May through July, but sporadically as late as November. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="W. L. Wagner, Hoch &amp; Zarucchi" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="W. L. Wagner, Hoch &amp; Zarucchi" baseAuthorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Onagraceae" genus="Oenothera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Oenothera hispida" order="Myrtales" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hispida">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">Oenothera hispida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
grows in sandy loam soils from the eastern half of Texas south through Mexico as far south Oaxaca. It is naturalized in Arkansas (Sevier Co.), coastal southern California, Georgia (Glynn Co.); its current status in both Arkansas and Georgia should be verified. It is considered an invasive species in California.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="27">
<taxonomicName authorityName="W. L. Wagner, Hoch &amp; Zarucchi" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="W. L. Wagner, Hoch &amp; Zarucchi" baseAuthorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Onagraceae" genus="Oenothera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Oenothera hispida" order="Myrtales" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hispida">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">Oenothera hispida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the sole member of 
<taxonomicName authority="Xenogaura" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Onagraceae" genus="Oenothera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Oenothera subsp. subsection" order="Myrtales" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSection" section="Gaura" species="hispida" subSection="Xenogaura" subSpecies="subsection">Oenothera sect. Gaura subsection Xenogaura</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Raven, PH" journalOrPublisher="Mem. Torrey Bot. Club" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" pagination="1 - 96" refId="B6" refString="Raven, PH, Gregory, DP, 1972. A revision of the genus Gaura (Onagraceae). Mem. Torrey Bot. Club 23: 1 - 96" title="A revision of the genus Gaura (Onagraceae)." volume="23" year="1972">Raven and Gregory (1972)</bibRefCitation>
suggested that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="W. L. Wagner, Hoch &amp; Zarucchi" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="W. L. Wagner, Hoch &amp; Zarucchi" baseAuthorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Onagraceae" genus="Oenothera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Oenothera hispida" order="Myrtales" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hispida">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">Oenothera hispida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
arose following interspecific hybridization between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="W. L. Wagner &amp; Hoch" authorityYear="2007" baseAuthorityName="Ser." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Onagraceae" genus="Oenothera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Oenothera suffrutescens" order="Myrtales" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="suffrutescens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">Oenothera suffrutescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Ser.) W.L.Wagner &amp; Hoch (subsect. 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Onagraceae" genus="Oenothera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Myrtales" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSection" subSection="Campogaura">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">Campogaura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(P. H. Raven &amp; D. P. Gregory) W.L.Wagner &amp; Hoch) and a species in subsect. 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Onagraceae" genus="Oenothera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Myrtales" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSection" subSection="Stipogaura">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">Stipogaura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(P. H. Raven &amp; D. P. Gregory) W.L.Wagner &amp; Hoch, possibly near 
<taxonomicName authorityName="W. L. Wagner &amp; Hoch" authorityYear="2007" baseAuthorityName="Munz" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Onagraceae" genus="Oenothera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Oenothera mckelveyae" order="Myrtales" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mckelveyae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">Oenothera mckelveyae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Munz) W.L.Wagner &amp; Hoch. 
<bibRefCitation author="Hoggard, GD" journalOrPublisher="Amer. J. Bot." pageId="3" pageNumber="28" pagination="139 - 148" publicationUrl="10.3732/ajb.91.1.139" refId="B3" refString="Hoggard, GD, Kores, PJ, Molvray, M, Hoggard, RK0, 2004. The phylogeny of Gaura (Onagraceae) based on ITS, ETS and TrnL-F sequence data. Amer. J. Bot. 91: 139 - 148, DOI: 10.3732/ajb.91.1.139" title="The phylogeny of Gaura (Onagraceae) based on ITS, ETS and TrnL-F sequence data." url="10.3732/ajb.91.1.139" volume="91" year="2004">Hoggard et al. (2004)</bibRefCitation>
found that the pistillate parent of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="W. L. Wagner, Hoch &amp; Zarucchi" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="W. L. Wagner, Hoch &amp; Zarucchi" baseAuthorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Onagraceae" genus="Oenothera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Oenothera hispida" order="Myrtales" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hispida">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">Oenothera hispida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was indeed 
<taxonomicName authorityName="W. L. Wagner &amp; Hoch" authorityYear="2007" baseAuthorityName="Munz" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Onagraceae" genus="Oenothera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Oenothera mckelveyae" order="Myrtales" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mckelveyae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">Oenothera mckelveyae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or a close relative, but that the staminate parent probably came from a lineage related to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Krakos &amp; W. L. Wagner" authorityYear="2013" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Onagraceae" genus="Oenothera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Oenothera dodgeniana" order="Myrtales" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dodgeniana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">Oenothera dodgeniana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Krakos &amp; W.L.Wagner or 
<taxonomicName authorityName="W. L. Wagner &amp; Hoch" authorityYear="2007" baseAuthorityName="Engelm. &amp; A. Gray" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Onagraceae" genus="Oenothera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Oenothera lindheimeri" order="Myrtales" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lindheimeri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">Oenothera lindheimeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Engelm. &amp; A.Gray) W.L.Wagner &amp; Hoch in subsect. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="W.L.Wagner &amp; Hoch" authorityYear="2007" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Onagraceae" genus="Oenothera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Myrtales" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSection" subSection="Gaura">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">Gaura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(L.) W.L.Wagner &amp; Hoch. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="W. L. Wagner, Hoch &amp; Zarucchi" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="W. L. Wagner, Hoch &amp; Zarucchi" baseAuthorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Onagraceae" genus="Oenothera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Oenothera hispida" order="Myrtales" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hispida">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">Oenothera hispida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not easily distinguished morphologically from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="W. L. Wagner &amp; Hoch" authorityYear="2007" baseAuthorityName="Ser." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Onagraceae" genus="Oenothera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Oenothera suffrutescens" order="Myrtales" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="suffrutescens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">Oenothera suffrutescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(subsect. 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Onagraceae" genus="Oenothera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Myrtales" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSection" subSection="Campogaura">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">Campogaura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), with which it shares the character of a thick stipe, and occasionally hydridizes in Texas. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="W. L. Wagner, Hoch &amp; Zarucchi" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="W. L. Wagner, Hoch &amp; Zarucchi" baseAuthorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Onagraceae" genus="Oenothera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Oenothera hispida" order="Myrtales" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hispida">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">Oenothera hispida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is an aggressively rhizomatous perennial with fruits conspicuously bulging on the distal half (
<bibRefCitation author="Raven, PH" journalOrPublisher="Mem. Torrey Bot. Club" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" pagination="1 - 96" refId="B6" refString="Raven, PH, Gregory, DP, 1972. A revision of the genus Gaura (Onagraceae). Mem. Torrey Bot. Club 23: 1 - 96" title="A revision of the genus Gaura (Onagraceae)." volume="23" year="1972">Raven and Gregory 1972</bibRefCitation>
). Since 
<taxonomicName authorityName="W. L. Wagner, Hoch &amp; Zarucchi" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="W. L. Wagner, Hoch &amp; Zarucchi" baseAuthorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Onagraceae" genus="Oenothera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Oenothera hispida" order="Myrtales" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hispida">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">Oenothera hispida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="W. L. Wagner &amp; Hoch" authorityYear="2007" baseAuthorityName="Ser." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Onagraceae" genus="Oenothera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Oenothera suffrutescens" order="Myrtales" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="suffrutescens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">Oenothera suffrutescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be difficult to distinguish we have included a capsule of the latter in the figure (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Oenothera hispida (Bentham) W. L. Wagner, Hoch &amp; Zarucchi A Habit, Mexico, Nuevo Leon, Roybal 34 (US) B Flower, lateral view, Roybal 34 (US) C Flower, face view, digital image (Ray Pistrum as &quot; Gaura drummondii fresh flower &quot; [http: // redsgoodvsevilcowbarn. blogspot. com / 2012 / 06 / chigger-chow-and-gaura-drummondii. html]) D Base of staminal filaments showing basal scales, Roybal 34 (US) E Capsule, Texas, Hall 213 (US) F Oenothera suffrutescens (Ser.) W. L. Wagner &amp; Hoch capsule, New Mexico, Standley 6481 (US)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.50.4886.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/44197" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">1</figureCitation>
-F) for comparison of key features for correct separation of the two species. The rhizomatous habit makes this species potentially invasive, despite its self-incompatibility, but so far it has established itself most aggressively only in coastal southern California (
<bibRefCitation author="Wagner, WL" journalOrPublisher="Syst. Bot. Monogr." pageId="3" pageNumber="28" pagination="1 - 240" refId="B7" refString="Wagner, WL, Hoch, PC, Raven, PH, 2007. Revised classification of the Onagraceae. Syst. Bot. Monogr. 83: 1 - 240" title="Revised classification of the Onagraceae." volume="83" year="2007">Wagner et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
). There are no other Hartweg collections of this species that anyone has seen other than the one cited above as the type collection. We have seen the holotype as an image on the Kew web site that was mistakenly filed under 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Onagraceae" genus="Gaura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Gaura coccinea" order="Myrtales" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="coccinea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">Gaura coccinea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Pursh. The label information corresponds to the published locality given and is marked as in the Bentham herbarium.
</paragraph>
